Two people were shot dead by bandits in Inyanzae village, Ngomeni location, Kyuso district, on Friday.The armed bandits are believed to be from either Tana River or the Northeastern region. The incident brings to three the number of people killed by the bandits during the holidays.Yesterday, Ngomeni MCA Nzungi Ngwele gave the names of those killed as Simon Matei, Musomba Makio and Kimwele Murami. Makio and Murami were killed during the day as they grazed their cattle. He said the bodies were taken by the police.The MCA said the attack has triggered an exodus as people are fleeing their homes. Residents of the neighbouring Kasiluni village have also taken off.